to the editor in can power transcend knotted silk big city column dec 1 john tierney notes that neckties and business suits are still de rigueur for lawyers and bankers and may one day be in vogue again for all white collar men i have eschewed neckties since right after world war ii when more formal attire was customary as a socratic scientist challenging accepted shibboleths i respond to criticism by saying a tie is the noose of conformity that society places around the neck of the individualist julian kane great neck ny dec 2 2000 the writer is a professor of environmental geology hofstra university

